  "title": "Technical Sales Engineer",
  "description": "<p>Our client is a world leading <strong>laser equipment manufacturer</strong>.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Drive sales of semiconductor equipment to meet or exceed sales targets</li><li>Engage in system, parts, and materials evaluations with customers</li><li>Manage customer inquiries, RFQs, and prepare sales proposals and quotations</li><li>Build and maintain strong customer relationships by understanding their needs and offering tailored solutions for long-term partnerships</li><li>Collaborate with customers and internal R&D teams on activities including presentations, quotations, specification alignment, negotiations, equipment commissioning/acceptance, and post-sales support</li><li>Take ownership of sales negotiations and deal closures</li><li>Develop and implement strategies to grow market share for assigned products and services</li><li>Generate and maintain sales reports for internal stakeholders</li><li>Ensure prompt and effective responses to customer inquiries</li><li>Undertake additional responsibilities as assigned by the management team</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>At least 10 years of sales experience, preferably in the semiconductor industry</li><li>Minimum diploma in Engineering or related field</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Office applications</li><li>Highly driven, resourceful, creative, and self-motivated</li><li>Excellent communication skills</li><li>Well-organized, detail-oriented, and able to manage multiple tasks effectively</li><li>Willing to work outside standard office hours and travel overseas when required</li><li>Capable of working independently as well as collaboratively within a team</li></ul><p>Our client offers attractive base + commission for the right candidate.</p><p><br /></p><p>By sending your job resume to us, it shall be deemed that you have agreed and hereby give your consent to Merries Employment LLP in collecting, using and/ or disclosing your personal data for the purpose of accessing and processing your job application and/ or for future job opportunities within Merries and/ or with the client(s) of Merries. If you wish to withdraw your consent, please notify us.<br /><br />We regret to inform only shortlisted candidates will be notified.<br /><br />Merries Employment LLP<br />EA Licence No: 14C7362</p><p>Posting Personnel: Jasmine Chew<br />EA Personnel Registration No: R1769441</p>",
